comments: I realised that the beginig of the word told you the shape, and the end of the word was the colour. i trie to write down spellings, but it was too fast, so I then tried to capture the end part of the word like su was yellow and ae was pink and fo was blue and pha was grey (although it sounded like sha), and I drew pictures of the shapes as best I could during the time when I realised the shapes were the beginning of the words; so a pentagon with buvi in it and a circle with wopi in it and a star with zeti in it. I've never been any good at spelling so think it would take a lot of repitition to get the spellings right when the sounds don't match if that makes sense. Spelling was the hardest part for me. Learning the colours was the easiest.
